title: 820-4924-A 220ma
message: Board was drawing 14ma initially pp5v_s3 was partially short, c7600 was reading 2v, so removed C7600 and u7600 5v  was present. After swapping out both components unit rises to 200ma . L7320 and L7310 both read .5 ohm . Would it be safe enough to say the cpu is dead on this?

title: 820-4924-A 220ma
message:
0.5 ohm means shorted CPU...

Easy to confirm, injecting voltage (no more than 2V), with heatsink removed.

title: 820-4924-A 220ma
message: I tried that but its actually not heating

title: 820-4924-A 220ma
message:
Do you have a good PSU?
5A PSU doesn't help now.
At least try starting with 1V and maintain current under PSU limit.

Get 20A PSU for injecting voltage!!!
